profile_positions.description:
Quantifying the environmental impact will benefit the sustainability of products, because a well founded decision is for sure a better one than a decision based on gut feeling. There is growing recognition in society that we need to comprehensively re-examine the sustainability of agro-food production, encompassing food, animal feed, non-food and energy products. Blonk Consultants was established to raise awareness and understanding of these environmental issues and to help public and private organisations make balanced and well-considered policy and business decisions. We believe this will not only raise the sustainability of agricultural production chains, but also of society as a whole. In short, Blonk Consultants gives shape to sustainability in the agro-food sector.

My work revolves around Life Cycle Assessment (LCA) and agricultural- and food products. LCA is an analytical tool to evaluate the environmental impact of a service or product. Based on LCA I work on: 
- Analysis of the environmental impact of agricultural- and food products;
- Life Cycle Assessment methodology development (e.g. PEFCRs);
- Life Cycle Inventory database development (e.g. Agri-footprint, Agribalyse, RIVM database);
- Tool development for specific food industries;
- Environmental evaluation of innovative products.
I also develop and organise trainings on LCA of agricultural and food products.

In my work I have a special focus on sustainable nutrition, combining the environmental impact of food products with the nutritional content and analyzing future healthy and sustainable diets and food product innovations.
